cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as depth and surface normal estimation from a single image using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a self-supervised learning framework, which involves training the networks without explicit supervision, making it relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of soft-constraints to train the networks also involves optimization techniques, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also proposes a novel approach to predicting depth and surface normals, which could be relevant to the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GR (Graphics).
